  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1982-05-04", 
    "text": "States that the United States and the Soviet Union should: (1) pursue a complete halt to the nuclear arms race; (2) decide when and how to achieve a mutual and verifiable freeze on the testing, production, and further development of nuclear warheads, missiles, and other delivery systems; and (3) proceeding from this freeze, pursue major, mutual, and verifiable reductions in nuclear warheads, missiles, and other delivery systems."
